OL,3,CInterest rates held at 5.25% but Bank
OL,4,Cof England 'optimistic' about cuts
OL,6,FThe Bank of England has decided to
OL,7,Fkeep UK interest rates unchanged, but
OL,8,Fgave a new sense of optimism that
OL,9,Fborrowing costs could soon be cut if
OL,10,Finflation is reined in.
OL,12,FWhile the central bank voted to hold
OL,13,Frates at 5.25%, governor Andrew Bailey
OL,14,Fsaid he is "optimistic that things are
OL,15,Fmoving in the right direction".
OL,17,FMr Bailey said there has been
OL,18,F"encouraging news" on inflation, which
OL,19,Fthe Bank expects to come close to its
OL,20,F2% target between April and June.
