OL,3,CInterest rates held at 5.25% but Bank
OL,4,Cof England 'optimistic' about cuts
OL,6,FMeanwhile, the Bank of England
OL,7,Fslightly upgraded its forecast for UK
OL,8,Feconomic growth.
OL,10,FIn its latest Monetary Policy Report,
OL,11,Fit said gross domestic product (GDP)
OL,12,Fwill increase 0.5% this year and 1% in
OL,13,F2025, both 0.25 percentage points
OL,14,Fhigher than the last estimates
OL,15,Fpublished in February.
OL,17,FThe improved outlook reflects higher
OL,18,Festimates for population growth, which
OL,19,Fwill boost productivity, as well as
OL,20,Fenergy costs coming down.
