OL,3,CInterest rates held at 5.25% but Bank
OL,4,Cof England 'optimistic' about cuts
OL,6,FIt also expects some positive impact
OL,7,Ffrom the Government's recent tax cuts,
OL,8,Fwhich is set to boost GDP by more than
OL,9,F0.25 percentage points compared with
OL,10,FFebruary projections.
OL,12,FOver the next few years, CPI inflation
OL,13,Fis expected to fall to a lower level
OL,14,Fthan prior predictions, dropping below-
OL,15,Ftarget to 1.5% across 2026.
OL,17,FIn the shorter-term, CPI is set to hit
OL,18,Fthe 2% target between April and June,
OL,19,Fbefore rising to 2.6% by the end of
OL,20,Fthe year.
